TY  - JOUR
T1  - On the Equivalence of Bayesian and Dominant Strategy Implementation
AU  - Gershkov, Alex
AU  - Goeree, Jacob K.
AU  - Kushnir, Alexey
AU  - Moldovanu, Benny
AU  - Shi, Xianwen
Y1  - 2013/01/01
PY  - 2013
DA  - 2013/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA10592
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 197
EP  - 220
VL  - 81
IS  - 1
KW  - Bayesian implementation
KW  - dominant strategy implementation
KW  - mechanism design
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA10592
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We consider a standard social choice environment with linear utilities and independent, one-dimensional, private types. We prove that for any Bayesian incentive compatible mechanism there exists an equivalent dominant strategy incentive compatible mechanism that delivers the same interim expected utilities for all agents and the same ex ante expected social surplus. The short proof is based on an extension of an elegant result due to Gutmann, Kemperman, Reeds, and Shepp (1991). We also show that the equivalence between Bayesian and dominant strategy implementation generally breaks down when the main assumptions underlying the social choice model are relaxed or when the equivalence concept is strengthened to apply to interim expected allocations.
ER  - 

