JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 315
EP  - 340
VL  - 81
IS  - 1
KW  - Semiparametric estimation
KW  - generated regressors
KW  - asymptotic variance
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA9609
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We study the asymptotic distribution of three-step estimators of a finite-dimensional parameter vector where the second step consists of one or more nonparametric regressions on a regressor that is estimated in the first step. The first-step estimator is either parametric or nonparametric. Using Newey's (1994) path-derivative method, we derive the contribution of the first-step estimator to the influence function. In this derivation, it is important to account for the dual role that the first-step estimator plays in the second-step nonparametric regression, that is, that of conditioning variable and that of argument.
ER  - 

